equation_narrative.headline: Polar representation solidifies through structural contacts, T emerges decisively in final layers
equation_narrative.story: Through layers 1-23, the model assembles a representation of position 7 by reading 7 structural contacts and 3 co-evolving positions, building a polar-leaning context. The logit lens shows early volatility—S leads initially (22.6% at L0), then cycles through H, Y, and N as different aspects of the local chemistry are encoded. N dominates the mid-layers (32.7% at L23), reflecting the polar character of the assembled context. The decisive shift occurs at L29-33: T-specific MLP neurons activate strongly (6.37 total projection at L29, 10.89 at L30), and T surges from 14% to 97.66% in the final four layers, overwhelming N which collapses from 28.6% to 0.4%.

perception_phase.summary: Layers 1-23 gather contextual information through structural and co-evolutionary channels. Early attention heads (L8:6 with 3.92 projection, L9:3 with 2.63 projection) write without clear structural sources, suggesting abstract feature encoding. By mid-layers, the representation stabilizes around polar character—N reaches 32.7% at L6 and maintains 32.15% at L23, while hydrophobic candidates (V, I, A) cycle through the logit lens as the model encodes local hydrophobic neighbors (QIFVK context). SAE features at L9 show high activation (F9:5728 at 49.47 projection, F9:1281 at 45.65), encoding the local sequence environment. The representation character is polar-leaning but chemically ambiguous, consistent with a position that must balance hydrophobic neighbors with polar functionality.
perception_phase.context_character: By L23, the model has assembled a polar-leaning representation consistent with a position in a mixed chemical environment—flanked by hydrophobic residues (I, F, V, L) but requiring polar character. The 7 structural contacts and 3 co-evolving positions provide moderate evolutionary constraint.
key_information_sources: Structural contacts: 7 residues within contact distance, read primarily through L31:11 (4.15 projection, 13% structural attention) and L32:16 (-4.80 projection, 18% structural attention)
Co-evolutionary signal: 3 coupled positions, with L31:17 showing 28.7% co-evolutionary attention (2.31 projection)
Local sequence encoding: L1 features (F1:5480, F1:9146, F1:1508 all >44 projection) capture immediate QIFVK[T]LTGKT context
Abstract chemistry: L9 features encode polar/hydrophobic balance, with representation cycling through N, H, Y as different chemical aspects are weighted

decision_phase.summary: The decision crystallizes at L29-33 through massive MLP neuron activation favoring T. At L29, T-specific neurons (N29:1291 with 0.88 projection, N29:4973 with 0.86 projection, N29:2564 with 0.65 projection) drive T from 14% to 31%. This acceleration continues through L30 (10.89 total MLP projection) and L31 (11.24 total projection), with neurons like N30:1323 (0.89 projection) and N31:3485 (1.04 projection) casting decisive votes. By L32, T reaches 82%, and the final layer pushes it to 97.66% as SAE features F33:2632 (124.9 projection) and F33:3356 (109.6 projection) activate strongly.
decision_phase.transition: The L23-25 boundary marks the shift from perception to decision. At L23, the representation remains ambiguous (N at 32.15%, T at 14%), with MLP neurons showing mixed signals (total projection -0.82). At L24, T-specific prediction channels first activate: N24:2402 projects 0.77 toward T with high specificity, and SAE features (F24:5827 at 12.01 projection) begin encoding T-specific patterns. The representation transitions from 'polar character in mixed environment' to 'threonine specifically.'

candidates.narrative: T emerges decisively in the final layers after being subdued through the perception phase. At L23, T sits at only 14%, but L29-33 see explosive growth driven by highly specific MLP neurons. N29:1291 (0.88 projection, top vote for T), N29:4973 (0.86 projection), and N30:1323 (0.89 projection) cast strong votes, pushing T from 31% at L29 to 97.66% at L33. The final layer's SAE features (F33:2632 at 124.9 projection, F33:3356 at 109.6 projection) represent T-specific prediction channels that consolidate the decision.
candidates.key_layers: Emerges at L29 (31%), dominant by L32 (82%), final 97.66%
key_evidence: N29:1291 (0.88 proj) — strongest T vote in critical acceleration layer
N30:1323 (0.89 proj) — sustains T momentum through L30
F33:2632 (MLP, 124.9 proj) — final-layer T-specific prediction channel
Total MLP projection: 6.37 at L29, 10.89 at L30, 11.24 at L31

candidates.narrative: N dominates the perception phase, reaching 32.67% at L6 and maintaining 32.15% at L23, reflecting the polar character of the assembled representation. However, N lacks decision-phase support—it peaks at 28.63% at L29 before collapsing to 0.4% at L33. The representation was N-leaning because the model encoded polar functionality, but once T-specific neurons activate (L29+), N is actively suppressed by erasers like N30:646 (-0.53 projection, with 0.84 vote against N).
key_evidence: Logit lens: 32.67% at L6, 32.15% at L23 — reflects polar representation character
N30:646 (MLP, -0.53 proj) — erases N with 0.84 vote against it
No N-specific prediction channels activate in decision phase

candidates.narrative: I peaks at 12.8% at L19, reflecting the hydrophobic character of the local sequence context (IFVK neighbors). The logit lens projects toward I when the model encodes the surrounding hydrophobic residues, but this is a representation artifact—I never receives decision-phase support. By L29, I drops to 1.49% and finishes at 1.16%, as the model commits to polar functionality over hydrophobic packing.
key_evidence: Logit lens peak at L19 coincides with hydrophobic neighbor encoding
No I-specific MLP neurons or SAE features in decision phase

candidates.narrative: S leads at L0 (22.59%), likely reflecting the embedding's prior for small polar residues in this sequence context. However, S drops sharply to 4.17% by L8 as the model reads structural contacts and realizes the position requires more than simple polarity. S briefly resurges to 9.59% at L29 but is ultimately suppressed, finishing at 0.18%.
key_evidence: Initial embedding bias toward small polar residues
No structural or co-evolutionary support in perception phase

turning_points.description: The representation shifts from the embedding's S-bias (22.59% at L0) to encoding local chemistry. Attention heads L8:6 (3.92 projection) and L9:3 (2.63 projection) write without clear structural sources, suggesting abstract feature computation. The logit lens cycles through H (43.9% at L7) and A (16.9% at L9) as the model encodes different aspects of the hydrophobic/polar balance. SAE features at L9 (F9:5728 at 49.47 projection) capture this mixed chemical environment.

The representation stabilizes around polar character. N rises from 13% at L15 to 32.15% at L23, while hydrophobic candidates (V, I, A) cycle through as the model continues to encode structural contacts. Attention head L13:17 (2.19 projection) and velocity events at L13 (8.91 total delta, 7.17 from attention) mark significant information flow. The representation is now 'polar-leaning in mixed environment' but not yet committed to a specific amino acid.

The decision phase: T surges from 14% to 97.66% through massive MLP activation. L29 contributes 6.37 total MLP projection, L30 adds 10.89, and L31 adds 11.24. Key neurons include N29:1291 (0.88 T-vote), N30:1323 (0.89 T-vote), and N31:3485 (1.04 T-vote). N collapses from 28.63% to 0.4% as erasers like N30:646 (-0.53 projection) suppress it. The final layer's SAE features (F33:2632 at 124.9 projection) consolidate T as the overwhelming winner.

deep_dives.label: Early SAE features (L1, L9)
deep_dives.caption: L1 features encode the immediate sequence context (QIFVK[T]LTGKT), with F1:5480, F1:9146, and F1:1508 all showing >44 projection. L9 features (F9:5728 at 49.47 projection) capture the mixed hydrophobic/polar environment as the model reads structural contacts.

deep_dives.label: Structural attention (L31-32)
deep_dives.caption: L31:11 (4.15 projection, 13% structural attention) reads structural contacts to support T, while L32:16 (-4.80 projection, 18% structural attention) erases competing candidates. L31:17 (2.31 projection, 28.7% co-evolutionary attention) incorporates evolutionary constraints.

deep_dives.label: Mid-layer SAE features (L18)
deep_dives.caption: L18 features show lower activation (F18:244 at 7.72 projection) compared to L1 and L9, suggesting the model is refining rather than accumulating new information. The representation character is stabilizing around polar functionality.

deep_dives.label: Decision SAE features (L24, L30, L33)
deep_dives.caption: L24 features (F24:5827 at 12.01 projection) mark the first T-specific prediction channels. L30 features (F30:5492 at 26.17 projection) amplify T during the acceleration phase. L33 features (F33:2632 at 124.9 projection, F33:3356 at 109.6 projection) are the final T-specific channels that push confidence to 97.66%.

deep_dives.label: MLP neurons L29-31
deep_dives.caption: The decisive layers: L29 contributes 6.37 total projection (N29:1291 at 0.88, N29:4973 at 0.86), L30 adds 10.89 (N30:1323 at 0.89), and L31 adds 11.24 (N31:3485 at 1.04). These neurons cast the votes that push T from 31% to 89%.

deep_dives.label: Final MLP layer (L32)
deep_dives.caption: L32 shows net negative projection (-3.3) despite strong T-writers (N32:516 at 1.16), because erasers like N32:1665 (-1.19 projection, voting for Y and H) suppress remaining competitors. The decision is already made; this layer cleans up residual probability mass.

equation_narrative.resolution: The model correctly predicts T by assembling a polar-leaning representation through L1-23, then activating T-specific MLP neurons in L29-33. The perception phase encodes 7 structural contacts and 3 co-evolving positions, building a representation consistent with polar functionality in a mixed chemical environment (reflected in N's 32% logit-lens probability at L23). The decision phase is decisive: T-specific neurons (N29:1291, N30:1323, N31:3485) contribute over 28 units of total MLP projection across L29-31, driving T from 14% to 89%. The strongest evidence is the coordinated activation of T-specific prediction channels in the final layers, with F33:2632 (124.9 projection) consolidating the 97.66% confidence.
